{
  "texts": [
    "[40] explore conditional prompt learning for vision-language models, enhancing multimodal capabilities.Building on these works, we propose Embodied Robotic Control Prompts (ERCPs).",
    "Ps are prompt templates composed of natural language commands c, text clarifications, and defined action primitives (APIs) to enhance safe task plan generation by LLMs.",
    "Large Language Models in RoboticsLarge Language Models (LLMs) have emerged as transformative tools in robotics, enabling multi-modal semantic understanding and enhancing robots' ability to interpret and interact with their environments.",
    "Recent advancements in fine-tuning and pre-training methods have improved LLMs' ability to process and integrate information across multiple modalities [41].A key strength of LLMs lies in their ability to leverage text descriptions to extract semantic information, facilitating a deeper understanding of environmental contexts.",
    "This capability enables robots to execute tasks through action primitives (APIs), ensuring more intuitive and adaptive interactions [42]."
  ]
}